goals.question: What is the distribution of flight delays?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the frequency of flight delays and the range of delay times.

goals.question: What is the average distance of flights?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the distribution of flight distances and identify any outliers.

goals.question: What is the most common origin airport?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us identify the airport with the highest number of flights and understand the distribution of flights across different airports.

goals.question: What is the relationship between delay and distance?
goals.visualization: Scatter plot of delay vs distance
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand if there is any correlation between flight delay and distance, and if longer flights tend to have more delays.

goals.question: What is the distribution of flights over time?
goals.visualization: Line chart of flights over time
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the trend of flights over time and identify any seasonality or trends in flight volume.

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='delay', bins=30, kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['delay'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['delay'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of flight delays?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Delay (minutes)")
    plt.ylabel("Frequency")
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.boxplot(data=data, y='distance')
    avg_distance = data['distance'].mean()
    plt.axhline(avg_distance, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Distance: {avg_distance:.2f}')
    plt.title('What is the average distance of flights?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    origin_counts = data['origin'].value_counts()
    chart = sns.barplot(x=origin_counts.index, y=origin_counts.values)
    plt.title("What is the most common origin airport?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Origin Airport")
    plt.ylabel("Number of Flights")
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.dates as mdates

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['date'] = data['date'].dt.date

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    flights_per_day = data.groupby('date').size().reset_index(name='count')
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='count', data=flights_per_day)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flights over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Flights')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(['Flights per Day'])

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
